Name: Notorotalia hornibrooki
Comment: ET: According to Bruce Hayward et al 1999 (their volume on shallow water benthics of New Zealand), this should be assigned to N hornibrooki.
Notes (change to Internal only notes?): According to Bruce Hayward et al 1999 (their volume on shallow water benthics of New Zealand) Notorotalia hornibrooki Hayward et al., 1999 is a different species from Notorotalia clathrata (Brady). They say that Vella 1957 identified a species as N clathrata (Brady), but did not show a picture, and they looked at Vella's material and new samples from where he described it, and say that what Vella identified is not N clathrata Brady. They give the name N hornibrooki to Vella's species (N clathrata Vella, not Brady), so there N clathrata in the literature (by Vella and people citing Vella) that according to Hayward et al should be assigned to N hornibrooki.
